WEBVTT

01:20.247 --> 01:22.874
RAY:
Everything's falling apart.

01:24.168 --> 01:26.753
And it all starts right here in Detroit...

01:27.421 --> 01:30.798
...the headwaters of a river of failure.

01:36.513 --> 01:41.350
Thank God my parents aren't around
to watch the country they loved go to shit.

01:42.561 --> 01:45.188
They were proud Americans.

01:45.606 --> 01:48.191
They had normal jobs
and made a normal living.

01:48.358 --> 01:50.318
They fit in.

01:51.195 --> 01:54.697
They weren't kicked up the ass every day
of their lives by property taxes...

01:54.865 --> 01:59.869
...and homeowners' associations
and greedy, beauty-queen ex-wives.

02:01.413 --> 02:05.917
What would I tell them if they saw me now?
That I'm not to blame? It's not my fault?

02:06.084 --> 02:08.377
They didn't raise me that way.

02:09.421 --> 02:14.342
They taught me to take responsibility
and get the job done. No excuses.

02:14.510 --> 02:18.179
You do your best with whatever gifts
God gave you.

02:18.347 --> 02:19.555
Anybody know what this is?

02:19.723 --> 02:22.225
And that's what I try to
teach my kids too.

02:24.019 --> 02:25.561
I'll give you a hint.

02:25.729 --> 02:29.065
It's a Scarabaeidea...

02:29.233 --> 02:31.567
Anybody here take Latin?

02:32.069 --> 02:34.237
It's a dung beetle, team.

02:34.404 --> 02:36.364
All right? So what's that make this?

02:37.407 --> 02:39.951
- Dung?
- Yes, it's dung, Schenken.

02:40.118 --> 02:41.160
[BOYS LAUGH]

02:41.328 --> 02:43.579
All right, but let's call it what it really is.

02:43.747 --> 02:46.415
It's a ball of shit.

02:46.708 --> 02:51.087
See, everywhere this little guy goes,
he takes his ball of shit with him.

02:51.255 --> 02:55.383
He eats it, he sleeps with it,
he talks to it at night.

02:55.551 --> 02:57.301
That's just how he's wired.

02:58.178 --> 03:00.721
So, what's the point
I'm trying to make here?

03:00.889 --> 03:02.807
- More man-to-man coverage?
- No, Jerry.

03:02.975 --> 03:06.936
What I'm trying to say
is that unlike this beetle...

03:07.104 --> 03:11.232
...we as a team cannot afford
to take our dung with us.

03:11.400 --> 03:15.611
We cannot roll it up into a ball.
We cannot push it up a hill.

03:15.779 --> 03:17.196
We shouldn't eat it.

03:17.364 --> 03:21.325
We certainly better leave it behind when
we get on the court against the Badgers.

03:21.493 --> 03:24.662
Shit happens. We know that.

03:24.830 --> 03:26.956
Rodelle's girl just broke up with him.

03:27.124 --> 03:29.750
Pazderka dropped a 40-pounder
on his foot.

03:29.918 --> 03:30.960
[BOYS LAUGH]

03:31.128 --> 03:34.422
One more D in Chemistry,
Kuzneski's ass is on the bench.

03:34.590 --> 03:36.382
"We got heart. We got hope."

03:36.550 --> 03:39.093
But it's not like we've been
winning any games, fellas.

03:39.261 --> 03:42.388
Just like last year,
it looks like every week...

03:42.556 --> 03:45.433
...we're gonna get our teeth kicked in.

03:46.602 --> 03:47.894
You okay, coach?

03:48.770 --> 03:50.354
Yeah, I'm fine.

03:50.564 --> 03:51.814
[RAY INHALES]

03:52.733 --> 03:54.150
[RAY EXHALES]

03:54.651 --> 03:56.485
All right.

03:57.195 --> 04:00.948
So tonight, let's leave our dung
in the locker room.

04:01.116 --> 04:04.827
Let's pretend we're on the winning streak
we're gonna start tonight.

04:04.995 --> 04:08.497
Let's go out there
and tear up some Badger ass.

04:08.665 --> 04:10.166
Come on. Let's do it.

04:10.334 --> 04:11.375
[ALL CHEERING]

04:11.543 --> 04:13.085
Wolves on three. One, two, three.

04:13.253 --> 04:14.545
ALL: Wolves!
- All right.

04:14.713 --> 04:17.131
- Let's go, guys.
- Let's go, guys. Let's go get them.

04:17.299 --> 04:19.550
- Let's go. Let's go.
- Go on, get them, Donovan.

04:19.718 --> 04:23.179
Come on. Let's go. Let's go, let's go.

04:23.347 --> 04:24.430
Go kick some ass.

04:24.598 --> 04:25.848
[CROWD CHEERING]

04:26.016 --> 04:27.141
Let's go.

04:27.309 --> 04:29.018
Oh, God.

04:29.186 --> 04:30.895
Ray? You okay?

04:31.063 --> 04:35.232
Yeah. It must be another kidney stone.
I can't believe this is happening now.

04:35.400 --> 04:38.527
- Should I call the nurse?
- No, I'll be all right. Just help me up.

04:38.695 --> 04:40.112
[MARCHING BAND PLAYING]

04:40.280 --> 04:42.782
Oh! God. Jesus.

04:42.950 --> 04:45.409
No, you're right. Better safe than sorry.

04:45.577 --> 04:49.455
I'm gonna drive myself to a hospital.
You go out there and run the system.

04:49.623 --> 04:51.332
I don't know the system like you do.

04:51.500 --> 04:54.710
Just put up some screens,
get the ball to Donovan. You'll do great.

04:54.878 --> 04:57.338
All right? I'll try to be back
by fourth quarter.

04:57.506 --> 04:59.507
Just go out there
and kick some ass, Mike. Go.

04:59.675 --> 05:01.300
[HORN BLOWS]

05:04.721 --> 05:06.722
MAN:
Let's do it, partner. Come on!

05:13.063 --> 05:14.563
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

05:26.493 --> 05:28.828
RAY:
Okay, so I lied.

05:29.371 --> 05:31.706
And I'm missing a game
during a losing season...

05:31.873 --> 05:34.000
...and I'm not proud of it.

05:34.584 --> 05:37.670
But desperate times
call for desperate measures.

05:37.838 --> 05:40.381
You know what a public school teacher
makes these days?

05:40.549 --> 05:44.093
Okay, so maybe we make a little more
in Michigan than the national average...

05:44.261 --> 05:48.597
...but what's the national average?
More than a waiter, less than a plumber.

05:48.765 --> 05:52.059
It's about half of what it takes
to live a normal life.

05:52.227 --> 05:54.729
So, what do you do
when your career pays crap?

05:54.896 --> 05:58.441
You do a side gig. Used to be stocks...

05:58.608 --> 06:01.777
...now eBay, maybe. Tutoring.

06:02.195 --> 06:06.490
Me, I've got a more unorthodox skill set.

06:06.658 --> 06:09.952
I'm in the oldest profession in the world.

06:10.704 --> 06:12.413
Well, I'm about to be.

06:12.581 --> 06:15.291
This is my first day on the job.

06:17.044 --> 06:20.129
Hey, it's been a rough couple of years.

06:20.297 --> 06:22.882
Really rough.

06:27.971 --> 06:31.015
It all started when Jessica
slapped me with a divorce.

06:31.183 --> 06:33.392
Twenty years, two kids...

06:33.560 --> 06:36.062
A real punch in the face.

06:36.229 --> 06:40.691
I had to kick the renters out and move into
my parents' house where I grew up.

06:41.485 --> 06:45.654
Only bright spot was the twins,
who said they'd rather live with me.

06:45.822 --> 06:49.784
Then came the kidney stone that
weirdly ended up in a prostate scare.

06:49.951 --> 06:51.327
Been having trouble urinating?

06:51.495 --> 06:54.205
Then the Wolves' unprecedented
losing streak...

06:54.372 --> 06:58.334
...which every week brings me
a new humiliation.

06:59.586 --> 07:02.505
And then this prick lawyer
moved in next door.

07:02.672 --> 07:05.716
I'd already been getting grief
from the homeowners' association...

07:05.884 --> 07:09.345
- Oh, hi.
...but this guy was a whole new level.

07:09.513 --> 07:11.847
- Howard Koontz.
- Ray Drecker.

07:12.015 --> 07:13.849
- Welcome to the neighborhood.
- Thank you.

07:14.017 --> 07:15.684
You sure got a swell spot.

07:16.311 --> 07:19.230
Say, I'm having a little open house
on Saturday.

07:19.397 --> 07:21.649
- Oh, that's very nice of you. Thank you.
- Yeah.

07:21.817 --> 07:23.984
So I was wondering
if between now and then...

07:24.152 --> 07:27.113
...you wouldn't mind tidying up
your lawn a little...

07:27.280 --> 07:29.907
...and, I don't know,
maybe cleaning out your gutters.

07:32.786 --> 07:36.497
Fucker had me hit with three citations
in the first six months alone.

07:36.957 --> 07:38.707
RAY: It's nice to meet you.
KOONTZ: You too.

07:38.875 --> 07:40.209
RAY:
Fucker.

07:41.211 --> 07:43.629
But nothing compared to this.

07:43.797 --> 07:45.798
[CLOCK TICKING]

08:35.140 --> 08:37.433
[FIRE ROARING]

08:44.065 --> 08:45.774
[GLASS BREAKING]

08:48.612 --> 08:50.112
DAMON:
Dad, wake up! Dad!

08:50.280 --> 08:52.948
- What?
- Dad, wake up!

09:07.464 --> 09:09.465
[CHATTER ON RADIO]

09:19.142 --> 09:21.393
Where the hell is she? Where is she?

09:21.561 --> 09:24.146
- She didn't say where she was going?
- Dad, I'm sure.

09:25.023 --> 09:26.732
Anybody seen my daughter?

09:28.777 --> 09:30.819
Hold on, I think this might be her.

09:30.987 --> 09:32.571
[CAR APPROACHING]

09:36.326 --> 09:37.826
Who's that?

09:38.328 --> 09:39.370
Um...

09:39.537 --> 09:41.830
It's, uh...

09:43.583 --> 09:46.168
- Where the hell have you been? Huh?
- Oh, my God!

09:46.336 --> 09:48.170
Oh, my God. Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

09:48.338 --> 09:50.673
RAY: It's all right.
They were able to contain the fire.

09:50.840 --> 09:53.050
Hey, you! Hey, you, come back here.

09:53.218 --> 09:55.135
Who is that?

09:55.303 --> 09:56.971
- It's Hammer.
- Hammer? Who's Hammer?

09:57.138 --> 09:59.139
- He's just a friend.
- Come on, Darb.

09:59.307 --> 10:02.768
Any guy named Hammer is not a good idea
at midnight. And your curfew is 10.

10:02.936 --> 10:04.979
What did I give you
a cell phone for, huh?

10:05.146 --> 10:08.274
What did we agree on?
You always keep the ringer on.

10:08.441 --> 10:11.026
You always answer when I call.
No excuses.

10:11.194 --> 10:12.861
- What did we say?
- The battery died.

10:13.029 --> 10:14.363
- No excuses!
- Dad, stop.

10:14.531 --> 10:17.032
- She's freaking out.
- The battery died.

10:17.367 --> 10:18.742
[RAY SIGHS]

10:21.079 --> 10:22.579
All right.

10:22.747 --> 10:25.040
All right, I'm sorry.

10:26.042 --> 10:27.543
All right, let's huddle up.

10:34.301 --> 10:35.884
All right.

10:36.386 --> 10:38.554
We're all right. Okay.

10:43.226 --> 10:45.227
Are you wearing lipstick?

10:45.395 --> 10:48.647
What is that? Answer me.

10:49.774 --> 10:51.608
What the hell's going on around here?

10:54.904 --> 10:56.905
Jesus.

10:57.907 --> 10:59.908
[SAW BUZZING]

11:05.248 --> 11:07.750
Hey, look, we're almost done here.

11:07.917 --> 11:09.793
You guys really ought to get some sleep.

11:09.961 --> 11:12.087
The insurance company will pay
for your hotel.

11:13.631 --> 11:15.299
We've got insurance, right?

11:17.594 --> 11:19.053
Of course we do.

11:19.220 --> 11:21.680
We're not staying in a hotel though.

11:22.098 --> 11:25.768
A burned-out house is a prime target
for thieves and vandals.

11:25.935 --> 11:28.771
We're staying here. Come on.

11:33.026 --> 11:35.986
We're gonna sleep right here
while we rebuild.

11:36.488 --> 11:39.615
Weather's not cold yet.
We get to be by the lake.

11:39.949 --> 11:43.118
It's gonna be great. We're gonna fish,
we're gonna cook breakfast.

11:43.286 --> 11:45.496
This'll be like camping,
only we're at home.

11:45.663 --> 11:48.207
You want all three of us
to sleep in the tent?

11:48.583 --> 11:51.335
I'll tell you what.
Today when we go shopping for clothes...

11:51.503 --> 11:54.004
...l'll buy you each your own tent.
How's that?

12:00.553 --> 12:03.806
- Are you calling Mom?
- Shit, yeah, I'm calling Mom.

12:05.475 --> 12:10.020
The fire. That's when I lost the kids.

12:15.235 --> 12:16.944
Nice day.

12:20.448 --> 12:23.492
What happened to my life?

12:25.829 --> 12:30.499
I used to be a big deal.
I used to be going somewhere.

12:31.876 --> 12:35.546
Now all I ever seem to do
is try not to drown.

12:35.713 --> 12:37.506
[BEEPS]

12:37.674 --> 12:41.135
When did life become
something you buy?

12:48.643 --> 12:52.187
[COUGHS]

13:32.312 --> 13:34.229
KOONTZ:
Say, Drecker?

13:34.731 --> 13:36.315
Drecker.

13:37.066 --> 13:39.401
You never responded to my offer.

13:40.236 --> 13:43.906
- These are tough times in real estate.
- Would you mind getting off my property?

13:52.040 --> 13:54.082
Just trying to do you a solid, Drecker.

13:54.584 --> 13:58.462
- This is a teardown if I've ever seen one.
- Hey, fuck off, Koontz.

14:00.507 --> 14:02.591
You know where to find me.

14:09.516 --> 14:11.850
I needed help.

14:20.235 --> 14:21.944
[SIGHS]

14:22.111 --> 14:24.112
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

14:34.707 --> 14:37.334
MAN: So this pregnant lady steps
into my office.

14:37.502 --> 14:38.961
She's got psoriasis, eczema...

14:39.128 --> 14:41.838
Dr. Ron Haxon, dermatologist.

14:42.006 --> 14:44.925
And she says, "Doctor, my sister thinks
I should try Accutane."

14:45.093 --> 14:48.220
Overcompensating little fucker
who stole my wife.

14:49.847 --> 14:51.515
Fucker.

14:52.642 --> 14:56.311
Lotte Brandt, my ex-mother-in-law.

14:56.479 --> 15:00.732
Looks sort of naked without
her breastplate and horned helmet.

15:01.776 --> 15:04.653
What's this you are doing here?

15:05.154 --> 15:06.196
Hi, Lotte.

15:06.614 --> 15:13.161
Does it feel good to you to almost murder
my grandchildren in your lethal house, huh?

15:13.329 --> 15:16.540
No, Lotte, it wasn't a good feeling.

15:16.708 --> 15:18.500
Why don't you just go away?

15:18.668 --> 15:20.669
- Mom. Mom?
LOTTE: Huh?

15:20.837 --> 15:23.338
Mom, relax. I can handle this.

15:23.506 --> 15:25.382
RAY: Hi, Jess.
- Ray.

15:25.550 --> 15:27.009
What are you doing here?

15:27.510 --> 15:31.722
Just being social.
Yeah, you always say, "Stop by, say hi."

15:31.889 --> 15:35.684
- So here I am. I'm just... I'm stopping by.
- Oh.

15:36.269 --> 15:39.938
- So how are the kids holding up?
- Kids are great. They're inside playing Wii.

15:40.106 --> 15:42.316
- Yeah?
- They're loving it here, Ray.

15:42.483 --> 15:45.694
- Don't you speak English? Go away.
- Mom, please.

15:45.862 --> 15:48.363
Ray's welcome.
We're just having a nice...

15:48.531 --> 15:50.824
...talk. We have no troubles here.

15:52.744 --> 15:54.536
She wasn't always like this.

15:54.704 --> 15:57.414
He's a doctor! He saves lives!

15:58.875 --> 16:00.959
How many fucking lives
have you fucking saved?

16:01.127 --> 16:03.170
He's a dermatologist.

16:03.338 --> 16:05.881
Come on, Jessica.
We went to school with the guy.

16:06.049 --> 16:08.550
- He's a turd. You know he's a turd.
- He loves me, Ray.

16:08.718 --> 16:10.719
- I love you.
- Not enough.

16:10.887 --> 16:13.764
- Put the fucking tulips back.
- Fuck off, Ray. They're my bulbs.

16:13.931 --> 16:16.224
Take the rose bushes.

16:17.477 --> 16:19.269
He's loaded. Is that it?

16:19.937 --> 16:24.024
Do you think I'm that shallow?
Do you really think I am that shallow?

16:24.192 --> 16:26.068
All right, yes, I am a little shallow.

16:26.402 --> 16:29.821
But I am deep enough to admit it.
I'm much deeper than people think, Ray.

16:29.989 --> 16:32.532
And I am only shallow
because I choose to be!

16:32.700 --> 16:34.368
I am a beauty queen, Ray.

16:34.786 --> 16:38.080
A homecoming, cheerleading,
stupid-ass beauty queen.

16:38.247 --> 16:40.123
And clearly, I made the obvious choice.

16:40.291 --> 16:45.337
Clearly, I was stupid enough
to have completely bought into it.

16:47.507 --> 16:50.050
What are you talking about?

16:51.177 --> 16:52.886
God, you were magical.

16:53.054 --> 16:56.098
- In high school, you were a king.
- King?

16:56.265 --> 16:59.017
You were beautiful and athletic...

16:59.185 --> 17:02.771
...and talented and smart and popular.

17:02.939 --> 17:04.439
And hung.

17:04.607 --> 17:06.942
What am I now, Jessica?
What am I now?

17:07.110 --> 17:09.736
Now you're just hung!

17:15.034 --> 17:19.621
So, Ray, is there a reason?
Is there something that you need?

17:19.789 --> 17:22.874
- Yeah. I...
- Uh-huh.

17:23.292 --> 17:25.627
Look, this is hard for me, okay?

17:25.795 --> 17:29.089
You know, I've never asked you
for anything before.

17:29.257 --> 17:32.801
I just need to... Uh...

17:34.095 --> 17:36.638
I need to borrow some money, okay?

17:36.806 --> 17:38.140
Well...

17:38.307 --> 17:41.351
Oh, my God, you're kidding.
That's why you came?

17:42.145 --> 17:45.313
What, they hiked your property taxes
or something?

17:45.481 --> 17:47.858
Yeah. That and this fire thing.

17:48.025 --> 17:51.862
It's really putting me
in a bit of a financial hole.

17:52.029 --> 17:55.365
- Ladies, enjoy.
- Oh, thanks. Thank you.

17:55.533 --> 17:58.660
- Well, did you talk to your claims adjuster?
- See, that's the thing.

17:58.828 --> 18:01.121
I mean, there's been some sort
of a mix-up.

18:01.289 --> 18:04.166
- You didn't let it lapse again, did you?
- No. I mean, sort of.

18:04.542 --> 18:08.420
I had the envelope right there on the desk,
ready to go out.

18:08.588 --> 18:10.130
- Jesus, Ray.
- L...

18:10.298 --> 18:12.632
- Hey there, Coach Ray.
- Hey, Ronnie.

18:12.800 --> 18:15.218
- Good to see you.
- Hi. How's the skin trade?

18:15.386 --> 18:17.679
I can't complain. Can't complain.

18:17.847 --> 18:20.307
Hey, I heard about your place, man.
That's tough.

18:20.767 --> 18:23.477
Yeah, thanks. I'm getting by.

18:23.686 --> 18:28.356
Just, you know, that house will be better
than ever once I make the repairs.

18:28.524 --> 18:31.151
RONNIE:
Glad to hear it. Just good to hear it.

18:32.028 --> 18:34.780
Hey, Ray, you might wanna have
that mole removed, you know?

18:35.072 --> 18:36.364
- Just to be safe.
- Yeah?

18:36.532 --> 18:40.035
Drop by the office any time.
Don't worry, free of charge.

18:40.203 --> 18:41.453
Good to see you, Ray.

18:44.957 --> 18:49.044
Look, I'm already screwed
with the property taxes, you know?

18:49.212 --> 18:53.799
Now I gotta find a way to fix the house
before the city slaps me with more citations.

18:53.966 --> 18:58.053
Plus, I got this jerkoff, this Koontz
sniffing around, trying to get me to sell.

18:58.221 --> 19:01.598
- And cheap too, you know.
- Sell. Sell the goddamn place, Ray.

19:01.766 --> 19:04.726
- Should have sold years ago.
- I'm not selling my parents' house.

19:04.894 --> 19:06.895
It's where I grew up.

19:07.063 --> 19:08.730
Look, what I'm saying is...

19:09.649 --> 19:13.527
...I got my back against
the wall here, okay?

19:14.237 --> 19:16.029
I'm in the Alamo.

19:16.739 --> 19:19.699
I'm not asking for a handout,
I'm asking for a loan, you know...

19:19.867 --> 19:21.952
...to tide me over.
- Right.

19:22.119 --> 19:24.746
I mean, if it was just me, l...
Shit, I wouldn't bother.

19:24.914 --> 19:29.084
- But I got the kids to take care of.
- You don't have the kids. I got the kids.

19:29.252 --> 19:32.170
- Well, until I fix the house.
- No, for good.

19:33.089 --> 19:36.800
They're gonna come back to me, Jessica.
I'm more fun and relaxed. You're uptight.

19:36.968 --> 19:40.762
Having more fun with you
almost got them killed.

19:46.143 --> 19:48.979
All right, forget I asked. Just forget it.

19:49.146 --> 19:51.773
- Okay.
- Just wipe it out of your mind.

20:13.713 --> 20:15.630
Ohh.

20:48.581 --> 20:51.791
Excuse me.
Is this "Unleash Your Inner Entrepreneur"?

20:51.959 --> 20:55.253
It is if you want it to be.

20:56.547 --> 20:59.424
FLOYD:
I'm going to tell you a secret right now.

21:00.051 --> 21:04.220
It's you. The secret is in you.

21:04.680 --> 21:09.225
Each one of you has already proven
that fact just by coming here tonight.

21:09.393 --> 21:12.187
And you are about to become
a millionaire.

21:12.355 --> 21:15.815
Repeat after me:
I'm going to be a millionaire.

21:15.983 --> 21:18.234
ALL [QUIETLY]: I'm gonna be a millionaire.
- No, no, no.

21:18.653 --> 21:21.655
I don't believe you at all.
Come on, we can do better than that.

21:21.822 --> 21:24.199
I'm going to be a millionaire.

21:24.367 --> 21:26.034
